The Top-of-Funnel Bottleneck (Funnel Analysis): The most critical drop-off point occurs immediately at the first step. Only 16.33% of Visitors convert into Leads (Stage 1 to Stage 2). Once users become Leads, the survival rate stabilizes drastically (44.7% convert to MQL, and 40.1% convert to SQL).
The "Golden Goose" vs. The "Money Pit" (Channel Efficiency): * LinkedIn is our most lucrative channel. It boasts the highest conversion rate (1.39%), the lowest CPA ($1,973), and an outstanding ROAS of 2.61x.
Conversely, Google Ads is severely underperforming, pulling in a negative ROAS (0.87x) with a sky-high CPA of $4,905.
Mobile Traffic is Bleeding Conversions (Device Analysis): Despite driving roughly 33% of all traffic (3,258 visitors), mobile users convert at a dismal 0.55%, compared to Tablet (0.97%) and Desktop (0.83%).
Empty Clicks in Brand Campaigns (Campaign Quality): The Brand_Awareness_2025 campaign successfully drives high traffic volume but brings in the lowest quality leads, converting at just 0.35%. Meanwhile, educational and urgency-driven campaigns like Webinar_Series_Tech and Flash_Sale_Feb drive the highest volume of actual Customers and SQLs.
